    "In fact, Sutton et al. (2019) identified 48 different review types, which they classified into seven review families (see Table 1).",
    "Although 10 According to the journal website on Springer Open (see Zawacki-Richter et al., 2019).",
    "part of the traditional review family, literature reviews have increasingly been influenced by the move to more systematic approaches, with many now including method sections, whilst still using the 'literature review' moniker (e.g., Alyahyan & Düştegör, 2020).",
    "Bibliometric analyses have also emerged as a popular form of evidence synthesis (e.g., Linnenluecke et al., 2020; Zheng et al., 2022), which analyse bibliographic data to explore research trends and impact.",
    "Whilst not included in the Sutton et al. (2019) framework, their ability to provide insight into a field arguably necessitates their inclusion as a valuable form of evidence synthesis."
  ]
}